1
00:00:06,070 --> 00:00:07,930
[All of Her]

2
00:00:08,230 --> 00:00:10,220
[Episode 3]

3
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:15,800
(Zhen.)

4
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:18,840
(Do not investigate our case.)

5
00:00:19,399 --> 00:00:21,319
(We made this choice out of desperation.)

6
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,560
[Commits Suicide]
(I'm so sorry.)

7
00:00:25,239 --> 00:00:27,000
(Please be healthy)

8
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:29,000
(and happy.)

9
00:00:37,439 --> 00:00:39,200
(Dad and Mom.)

10
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:40,400
(Don't worry.)

11
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,319
(I'm entering the file room)

12
00:00:42,319 --> 00:00:43,759
(tomorrow)

13
00:00:43,759 --> 00:00:45,479
(to find out the truth.)

14
00:00:46,639 --> 00:00:48,360
(No one can stop me,)

15
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:50,319
(neither Chu Ze'an)

16
00:00:50,959 --> 00:00:52,200
(nor Chu Zejia can.)

17
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,840
Look carefully.
Don't miss out on anything.

18
00:00:56,919 --> 00:00:57,639
Ms. Yan.

19
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:06,279
Have you got everything?

20
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:07,519
Let's go.

21
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:14,930
[File Room]

22
00:01:19,839 --> 00:01:20,919
I'm the CFO

23
00:01:20,919 --> 00:01:21,800
appointed by the group.

24
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,040
I didn't permit you
to investigate the ledger.

25
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,480
For the group's new development,

26
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:28,120
we must audit

27
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:29,760
all the ledgers, even from the past.

28
00:01:30,239 --> 00:01:31,639
I understand what you mean.

29
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,239
But you need to go through
the proper procedures

30
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:35,839
before auditing.

31
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,639
Since you understand,

32
00:01:37,919 --> 00:01:39,120
show your support, then.

33
00:01:43,519 --> 00:01:45,160
Did you forget

34
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,519
what you told me

35
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:49,239
yesterday afternoon?

36
00:01:59,239 --> 00:02:00,080
Or shall we

37
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:01,760
talk elsewhere?

38
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,000
Sure.

39
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,360
Yan Zhen.

40
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:09,720
Don't worry.

41
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:27,119
Go on, good guy.

42
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,039
What is that?

43
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:36,960
For your safety,

44
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,679
I briefly checked your place.

45
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:40,679
Don't worry.

46
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,520
I didn't enter your bedroom.

47
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,399
How did you know about the door code?

48
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,919
Don't tell me

49
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,800
your brother told you about this.

50
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,880
I thought you should
be more concerned about

51
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:57,000
who installed

52
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,679
these cameras.

53
00:02:59,839 --> 00:03:01,199
(I shall see)

54
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,720
(whether or not you're Chu Zejia.)

55
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,160
Aren't you

56
00:03:06,679 --> 00:03:08,679
overly concerned about my safety?

57
00:03:11,119 --> 00:03:13,240
I did it for the sake of
the company's safety.

58
00:03:13,399 --> 00:03:14,559
You shouldn't miss out on my bedroom.

59
00:03:17,639 --> 00:03:18,759
Why don't you come again

60
00:03:19,399 --> 00:03:21,039
at seven tonight?

61
00:03:21,279 --> 00:03:22,720
You trust me so much.

62
00:03:24,039 --> 00:03:25,399
Because you're a good guy,

63
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,919
just like your brother.

64
00:03:27,479 --> 00:03:28,039
Am I right?

65
00:03:33,759 --> 00:03:34,919
Stop investigating

66
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,399
the old ledgers.

67
00:03:37,399 --> 00:03:38,559
The access card is with me.

68
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,080
I won't give it to you.

69
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,000
With my permission,

70
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,880
you can't enter the file room.

71
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,399
(If you are him,)

72
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,520
(you will give yourself away.)

73
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:10,960
Xin.

74
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,040
[Anshi Group]
What are you doing here?

75
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,720
I'm here to see Yan Zhen.

76
00:04:14,478 --> 00:04:15,079
You can't go.

77
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:16,519
Everyone is working now.

78
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,880
Please let me in.

79
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:21,839
Listen.

80
00:04:22,119 --> 00:04:23,119
Don't let the woman

81
00:04:23,119 --> 00:04:26,079
be with Ze'an alone.

82
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,320
What if

83
00:04:27,399 --> 00:04:30,000
Ze'an disappears

84
00:04:30,359 --> 00:04:31,119
one day?

85
00:04:31,239 --> 00:04:32,000
I remember that you have a lecture class

86
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,959
this afternoon.

87
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:33,839
Let's go.

88
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:35,920
Come.

89
00:04:36,799 --> 00:04:37,359
Fine.

90
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:01,399
Good evening, Ze'an.

91
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:03,320
Welcome.

92
00:06:11,799 --> 00:06:12,679
I...

93
00:06:13,079 --> 00:06:13,920
Should I wear these?

94
00:06:14,799 --> 00:06:15,720
Everyone wears that.

95
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,000
Fine.

96
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,559
Quite an expert.

97
00:06:33,279 --> 00:06:34,320
But I was told

98
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:35,760
that you were passionate

99
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,079
about street art.

100
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,040
I'm tired of those.

101
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:40,239
So I move on to something new.

102
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,440
This looks new.

103
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:43,720
You just bought it?

104
00:06:44,119 --> 00:06:45,480
I bought this

105
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,959
especially for you.

106
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,959
Are you satisfied?

107
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,320
(Isn't this the access card
to the file room?)

108
00:06:56,799 --> 00:06:57,359
Zhen.

109
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,559
You want me
to check your bedroom, right?

110
00:07:00,839 --> 00:07:02,959
I'm also worried about the bathroom.

111
00:07:03,279 --> 00:07:04,119
Please check that for me.

112
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,519
Sure.

113
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,920
(Where did she get
these men's slippers?)

114
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,679
(Is she testing me?)

115
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,799
It's all good here.

116
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:55,959
Well.

117
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,320
Let's go to the bedroom.

118
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:04,880
Be thorough.

119
00:08:05,119 --> 00:08:06,040
Don't make me worry.

120
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:26,100
[Love you forever]

121
00:09:37,599 --> 00:09:39,200
The Count of Monte Cristo.

122
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,039
Zhen.

123
00:09:41,479 --> 00:09:42,359
You have fine taste.

124
00:09:42,679 --> 00:09:43,359
Did you read that before?

125
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,400
This is my favorite.

126
00:09:45,799 --> 00:09:47,320
The protagonist's revenge plan
is marvelous.

127
00:09:48,679 --> 00:09:49,960
Scan my bed, too.

128
00:09:54,799 --> 00:09:55,840
It's safe in your bedroom.

129
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,479
It may seem so.

130
00:09:59,719 --> 00:10:01,479
But since you're worried
about my safety,

131
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:02,799
why don't you stay here

132
00:10:02,799 --> 00:10:04,559
and be my bodyguard?

133
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,039
Why me?

134
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:13,880
Because you're Chu.

135
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:15,640
Having you around

136
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,239
is like having an amulet.

137
00:10:17,599 --> 00:10:18,520
It's safer.

138
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,799
I don't think

139
00:10:23,919 --> 00:10:25,280
you would want anything bad
to happen to me, right?

140
00:10:26,670 --> 00:10:29,980
♪Waiting for the wilted flower
to finally fall silent♪

141
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,119
But what benefits do I get

142
00:10:31,919 --> 00:10:33,080
as your bodyguard?

143
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:37,990
♪He stalks my mind and memories♪

144
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:40,820
♪Struggling in this perpetual cycle♪

145
00:10:41,940 --> 00:10:45,480
♪Promises are answering his lies♪

146
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:49,470
♪I'm just a walker-on
in this tear-jerker♪

147
00:10:49,780 --> 00:10:53,200
♪Tick, tock, tick, tock♪

148
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:56,000
♪Tears are speaking♪

149
00:10:57,190 --> 00:11:00,790
♪Mist blinds his eyes
from seeing rose graffiti♪

150
00:11:00,810 --> 00:11:04,620
♪The dialogue sounds hoarse,
I can only hide my words within♪

151
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:08,420
♪Love me, will you? Quiet, silly♪

152
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:11,560
♪Or just let it go?♪

153
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:16,080
♪My youth is like burning snowflakes♪

154
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:19,770
♪Your castle is fended♪

155
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:23,730
♪Let the heavy downpour
awaken the summer♪

156
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:26,890
♪I turn away from glamor♪

157
00:11:27,510 --> 00:11:31,250
♪Your garden is sown with fairy tales♪

158
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:35,130
♪I stay under the limp spring blossom♪

159
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:38,920
♪Trimming off all the mess♪

160
00:11:40,571 --> 00:11:43,021
[Human life is filled
with many pure, happy,]

161
00:11:43,022 --> 00:11:45,470
[serene examples of insincerity.
Osamu Dazai.]
